label: Original Concept
definition: Appearing in the earliest reference where a new name\u2013type association was established

label: Revisional Concept
definition: Appearing in a comprehensive revision of an existing taxonomic name and  lineage, e.g. a monograph, a species webpage, or a field manual with  descriptions and illustrations.

label: Relational Concept
definition: Appearing in a comprehensive hierarchy of concepts (typically without  descriptions and illustrations); therefore the meaning may be inferred  through parent/child relationships, or by examining the entire list of  mutually exclusive concepts.
examples: _Andropogon virginicus_ L. sec. ITIS (2006). [an on-line taxonomic service]

label: Informal Concept
definition: Appearing in a taxonomic treatment, but poorly specified (mentioned 'in  passing'), or merely implied, being outside of the discussion of the focal  names and taxa.
examples: _Andropogon hallii_ Hack. sec. Weakley (2006). [a Midwestern species]

label: Nominal Concept
definition: Appearing outside of the context of a particular source (without a sec.) and  indirectly linking to all other concepts in which the name occurs.
